# RTK — Rust Token Killer

`rtk` is a token-optimized CLI proxy for shell commands (60-90% token savings). Prefix output-heavy shell commands with `rtk` — but **never** use it as a substitute for the dedicated `grep`/`glob`/`read`/`background_process` tools (those are already token-aware). Full command reference, the rtk-vs-dedicated-tool table, and chained-command examples are in the **`rtk` skill** — load it when about to run build/test/lint/git-log/docker-style output-heavy commands.

